# Force LF line endings on shell scripts. Bash on Windows hates CRLF
# in .sh files -- the shebang fails with "/bin/bash^M: bad interpreter"
# and `then` / `fi` keywords mid-statement get treated as identifiers.
# Git's default autocrlf would normalize these to CRLF on checkout on
# Windows machines; this attribute keeps them LF regardless of the
# user's local autocrlf setting.
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf
